    <refname>IDCT</refname>
    <refpurpose>Compute inverse Discrete Transform of image</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   newimage = IDCT(image)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>image :</term>
      <listitem><para> floating-point image</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>new_image :</term>
      <listitem><para> IDCT of the input image</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
The IDCT function computes the inverse cosine transform of a floating-point image with even number of rows and columns.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

